        "uuid": "691f3755_553ecca4",
        "filename": "android/base/system/System.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 380,
      "author": {
        "id": 1000411
      },
      "writtenOn": "2015-09-14T21:39:04Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "TMP is not always defined, as far as I know, you\u0027re probably thinking about TMPDIR instead, which is mandated by Posix. We could indeed use it instead of the hard-coded /tmp/ below.\n\nANDROID_TMP is intentional, to specifically direct emulator\u0027s temporary files to a specific location, independent from other stuff (e.g. the emulator launches the \u0027ddms ping\u0027 command, or can launch external binaries like \u0027e2fsprogs\u0027, and probably more in the future). This is useful for debugging and troubleshooting only though. I propose we change this in a future patch too.",
      "parentUuid": "44725a92_285f935a",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 380,
        "startChar": 38,
        "endLine": 380,
        "endChar": 49
      },
      "revId": "a14343c8a8eb80c1217562238c0964023854f18d",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889",
      "unresolved": false
    },
